## Phase 1 detail — what's implemented but not yet committed

This is backend-only and has no user-facing surface, but it's worth being precise about scope since it's the immediate predecessor to any UI work:

- `authz.yaml` — new, explicit public-path / always-protected-path allow-list
- `libs/common/middleware.py` — rewritten to fail closed by default, mandatory JWKS verification, no silent exception swallowing
- `libs/common/service_auth.py` — new, service-to-service bearer-token verification for `ddp_engine`, `vdp_wedge`, `trust_graph`
- `libs/common/webhook_auth.py` — new, HMAC signature verification for the inbound `/invoices/captured` webhook
- `services/borrower_gateway/app.py` — OCEN JWS dev-bypass now gated to sandbox mode only; webhook signature check wired in
- `services/borrower_gateway/ops_api.py` — `OPS_API_KEY_FALLBACK_ENABLED` flag added (transitional, ahead of Phase 3's per-user login cutover)
- `tests/test_rbac_hardening.py`, `tests/test_service_auth.py` — 35 new tests, all passing; full existing suite (185 tests) verified with no regressions

**Status:** verified working, sitting in the working tree on `feat/rbac-and-role-uis`, not yet committed. (There is also unrelated, pre-existing uncommitted work on this branch — a Udyam-verification feature and a staged deletion of `sandbox/` — that predates this session and does not belong to this plan; it has been left untouched.)

